But that is not the only reason there should not be more then one party in PoS at any time.<br>
<br>
PoS is a huge pain in the butt! Island instruction, duel/summoning, dealing with keys, passing out loot... it  is all a pain... I cannot fathom having two raids try to fight for /ooc and /shout space. There are some zones where you can say soandso use ooc and we will use shout but PoS is chat intensive and this just won't work here. It would be a nightmare for everyone involved. <br>
<br>
The only solution I see is for the people wanting to go to PoS need to reserve a day NOT already taken by someone else. Then you don't have to worry about how far they went or how well they did. Get your own day, form your own raid, and go to it. My guild raids PoS more then anyone out there. We do 3 day raids because we like to farm some things. On a 3 day raid we do isle 1-4 on day 1 (fairies - horse/griffon...i do not count Dojorn as a numbered isle since you can skip it), on day 2 we redo 4 then farm 5 then clear 6 (bzzz), on day 3 we redo 6, clear 7, and kill the Eye if the Hand is not around. If we only want to go for epic stuff we grab a weeknight and just do epics. Last Wednesday we took 40 people up and farmed 5 till 3 wingblades dropped, cleared the bees, and cleared 7 hoping for mage crowns to drop(4 non-abyss mages needed crowns). None did... So I reserved PoS for tomorrow night and we're only going to 7.<br>
<br>
Is PoS wasted? Should someone else come up and clear 1-3?<br>
<br>
No. <p>Aislinn Darkenwald<br>
