<br>
I agree that 3 day reservations should not be made to reserve isle 1 and only isle 1.  I agree that folks who bite off more than they can chew should know when to say, &quot;enough, let someone else have Sky.&quot;  I agree that folks should be curtious to their servermates, and try to get along as best they can, communicate constructively before accusitorily, and come to reasonable compromises when they're is a conflict.  And I do mean reasonable, not &quot;get out of the plane, you're taking too long on your reserved days.&quot;<br>
<br>
Multiple raids in Sky seem impractical to me, unless two smaller guilds/raids that want to go up are in total agreement on all details.  It can't be effectively scheduled using only the calendar, and as Thoric mentioned, adds too many rules and potential for arguments and confusion.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't be objected to a 2 day reservation change personally.  Seeing what we were able to accomplish considering the limited number of resources we had at the time to rely on, I see no reason why a well balanced raid can't do 1 - 8 in 2 days. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leare</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/1/01 12:08:31 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=Http://member.aol.com/bushtfur/dagger Height=180 Width=50></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sky rule need to be changed with strong guide line</span><hr size=1> If you don't care for the opinion of a 25th Rogue don't read.<br>
<br>
If you reserved PoS for 3 days.  You can stay on island 1 all 3 days for all I care, and I still wouldn't consider it a waste.  Telling people they would have to make it to island 4 in a day, although not to hard, is just stupid.  Every other raid in PoS has followed the same rule, isle 1 - day 1, isle 1-4 - day 2, and isle 4-8 - day 3.  It's the way it's always been done and shouldn't be changed.<br>
<br>
It would be the same as tell someone who reserved the fg's if the can't get to the king don't reserve them.  And although we all know most people will kill King Tormax (Or however it's spell, you know who I'm talking about), but if they didn't should we call there raid a waste, I think not.  Or telling someone raiding Fear if they don't kill Cazic, then it's a waste.<br>
<br>
To tell anyone who rightfully reserved a zone that their raid was a waste or to say the zone went to waste for whatever reason is just ignorant. <p><img src=Http://member.aol.com/Bushtfur/Leare><br><br><i>"Anyone stupid enough to get close enough to inspect a Rogue deserves to walk away a little lighter<br><br>-Leare"</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessageRange?topicID=1638.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1645.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1647.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.threadControl?topicID=1638.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1638.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1638.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brell